==English==

=== Etymology ===
Comes from Middle English ''outlaue'' meaning "banished."

=== Noun ===
'''outlaw'''

#A [[fugitive]] from the [[law]].
#A person who is excluded from normal [[legal rights]].
#A [[wild horse]].

